# MapTanim: System Architecture & Design Documentation

This document provides a comprehensive breakdown of the conceptual, architectural, and system design components for **MapTanim**, a Web and Mobile-Based Geo-Mapping-Driven Inter-cropping Planning, Farm Management, and Agricultural Decision Support Platform. 

---

## 1. Conceptual Framework

MapTanim follows an **Input-Process-Output-Feedback (IPOF)** framework, designed to transform user inputs and environmental data into actionable agroecological guidance.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Inputs
        F[Farmer Data: Zones, Crops, Tasks]
        E[External API Data: Soil, Weather, Solar]
    end
    subgraph Processes
        C[Automatic Zone Classification]
        R[Agroecological Rule Engine Scoring]
        S[Strategic Layout & LER Simulation]
        G[Planting Calendar Generation]
    end
    subgraph Outputs
        R1[Ranked Crop Recommendations]
        T[Task & Planting Calendar]
        L[Strategic Farm Layouts]
        A[Analytics & Performance Dashboard]
    end
    subgraph Feedback
        F1[Farmer Task & Growth Logs]
        H[Actual Harvest & Yield Data]
    end
    
    Inputs --> Processes
    C --> R
    R --> S
    S --> G
    Processes --> Outputs
    Outputs --> Feedback
    Feedback -- Refines Models --> Processes
```

---

## 2. System Architecture

MapTanim employs a **Client-Server Architecture** optimized for resource-constrained environments.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Client[Client Tier\nProgressive Web App - Mobile/Web]
    App[Application Tier\nRESTful API Server & Rule Engine]
    Data[(Data Tier\nSpatial Database)]
    API[External Data Tier\n3rd Party APIs]
    
    Client <-->|HTTP/JSON| App
    App <-->|SQL/Geospatial Queries| Data
    App <-->|REST Requests| API
```

---

## 3. Hardware Architecture

The hardware architecture relies on cloud-based deployment to ensure high availability and scalability, minimizing the hardware burden on end-users.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph End-User Hardware
        Mob[Farmer Smartphone\nGPS Enabled, Mobile Data]
        PC[Officer/Admin PC\nDesktop Web Browser]
    end
    subgraph Cloud Infrastructure
        LB[Load Balancer]
        Web[Application Servers\nvCPU, RAM]
        DB[(Database Server\nSSD Storage)]
    end
    
    Mob --> LB
    PC --> LB
    LB --> Web
    Web --> DB
```

---

## 4. Software Architecture

MapTanim utilizes a **Modular Monolithic** software architecture.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Frontend PWA
        UI[User Interface / React]
        SW[Service Worker / Cache]
        MapFront[Web Map Interface]
    end
    subgraph Backend Server
        API[REST API Controllers]
        Logic[Business Logic & Rule Engine]
        MapBack[Spatial Processors]
        ORM[Database Connector]
    end
    
    UI --> SW
    UI --> MapFront
    SW <-->|Sync| API
    MapFront <--> API
    API --> Logic
    Logic --> MapBack
    Logic --> ORM
```

---

## 5. Network Architecture

The network architecture is designed for security and reliability over varying connection qualities (3G/4G/Wi-Fi).

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Client((Client Devices)) -- HTTPS/WSS --> FW[Firewall]
    FW --> LB[Cloud Load Balancer]
    LB --> App[Web/App Servers]
    App -- Secure Internal VPC --> DB[(Spatial Database)]
    App -- HTTPS --> Ext((External APIs))
```

---

## 6. Database Architecture

To accommodate the geospatial requirements of polygon zone drawing, MapTanim uses an Object-Relational Database with Spatial Extensions (e.g., PostgreSQL with PostGIS).

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Relational & Spatial Database
        subgraph Spatial Data
            Zones[(Zones / Polygons)]
        end
        subgraph Relational Data
            Users[(Users / Roles)]
            Farms[(Farms)]
            Crops[(Crop Library / Matrices)]
            Plans[(Plans & Tasks)]
        end
        Users --> Farms
        Farms --> Zones
        Zones --> Plans
        Crops --> Plans
    end
```

---

## 7. Application / Module Architecture

The system is compartmentalized into specific functional modules corresponding to the 15 phases.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Core[MapTanim Core System]
    Core --> Auth[Auth & Onboarding Module]
    Core --> GIS[GIS Mapping Module]
    Core --> Rule[Agroecological Rule Engine]
    Core --> Farm[Farm Operations Module]
    Core --> Anal[Analytics & LER Module]
    Core --> Collab[Community & Collab Module]
```

---

## 8. Security Architecture

Security features JWT authentication, Role-Based Access Control, and encrypted data in transit and at rest.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Client[Client App] -- HTTPS TLS 1.2+ --> WAF[Web Application Firewall]
    WAF --> Auth[Authentication Service\nJWT Validation]
    Auth --> RBAC{Role-Based Access Control}
    RBAC -- Farmer Access --> F_API[Farmer Endpoints]
    RBAC -- Admin Access --> A_API[Admin Endpoints]
    RBAC -- Officer Access --> O_API[Officer Endpoints]
    F_API --> DB[(Encrypted Database)]
    A_API --> DB
    O_API --> DB
```

---

## 9. Integration Architecture

How MapTanim connects to external scientific data sources.

